commits.commitMessage:
Enable open-source build of meta-mangoh layer

MangOH builds depended on sierra-m2m-init to install a version
file in /etc/legato. Since sierra-m2m-init is in meta-swi-extras,
this dependency prevented open-source builds of meta-mangoh layer.

With creation of /etc/legato/version moved to meta-swi, this
dependency is no longer needed and can be dropped, hence enabling
open-source builds of meta-mangoh.

Resolves: LXSWIREF-253
Change-Id: Icfaeff72fc1f24572896e6b3751e10a1a61aa71c
Related: LXSWIREF-241
Signed-off-by: Zoran Markovic <zmarkovic@sierrawireless.com>
commits.subject: Enable open-source build of meta-mangoh layer

commits.commitMessage:
Force LD path in ti-compat-wireless

It appears that on Ubuntu 12.04, python is loading the host libssl while
python-m2crypto is being built against a version provided by Yocto.

On newer Linux versions, the RPATH information from _m2crypto.so is
being used to load the lib from the Yocto environment, but this does not
appear to be the case on 12.04.

This workaround uses LD_LIBRARY_PATH to provide higher-prority-than-host
paths to load the libraries from the Yocto env.

Resolves: trac:4726
Change-Id: I095ecdfc68cb905c8eacdf65cf4f5ab2aa3f79d9
commits.subject: Force LD path in ti-compat-wireless

Fix invalid license warning from sierra-init-tiwifi

Package sierra-init-tiwifi refers to license MPL2.0.
Yocto provides the following warning:

WARNING: sierra-init-tiwifi: No generic license file exists for: MPL2.0
in any provider

The common license is actually known as MPL-2.0:
poky/meta/files/common-licenses/MPL-2.0

commits.commitMessage:
Update tiwifi script to work with IoT wifi DV2

Set GPIO33 and GPIO8 to 1 before loading msm_sdcc module.
Reset these GPIOs after unloading msm_sdcc_module.
Fix SDIO speed to max speed supported.

To work correctly, the AT commands:
    AT+WIOCFG=33,16
    AT+WIOCFG=8,16
    AT!RESET
should be applied to allocated GPIO 8 & 33 to app core.

Change-Id: I23efaeb21dd429218b1ccb41be176b1235b8781f
Resolves: #4500
commits.subject: Update tiwifi script to work with IoT wifi DV2
